accumulator; A variable used in a loop to add up or accumulate a result.
counter; A variable used in a loop to count the number of times something happened. 
decrement; An update that decreases the value of a variable.
increment; An update that increases the value of a variable (often by one).
infinite loop; A loop in which the terminating condition is never satisfied or for which there is no terminating condition.
indefinite loop (while); A loop that continues until a condition is met.
definite loop (for); A loop that continues until all known sets or conditons is completed.
iteration; Repeated execution of a set of statements using either a function that calls itself or a loop.